e\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530564\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ofh1665702943152.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ofh1665702943152.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ofh1665702943152.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ofh1665702943152\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Supported Utilities on Microsoft SQL Server\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ofh1665702943152__supported_utilities_on_microsoft_sql_server_154701\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The MSS connector supports the Create Table, Create Script, and Load Definitions facilities. For more information, see:\n </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofh1665702943152__li_d24572e1_d24573e1_d24574e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qkh1665702622728.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qkh1665702622728.html\" title=\"Uniface provides a command line facility for generating SQL script files to create database tables, and where applicable, indexes and stored procedures. These scripts can be used by database administrators to prepare the database for a Uniface application or a Uniface Repository.\">Create Table Facility</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofh1665702943152__li_d24575e1_d24576e1_d24577e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dln1665702622802.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dln1665702622802.html\">Create Script Facility</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofh1665702943152__li_d24578e1_d24579e1_d24580e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bnt1665702622573.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bnt1665702622573.html\" title=\"The IDE provides a facility for loading database table definitions from the data dictionary of the selected DBMS into the Uniface model. This is useful when you are creating a Uniface application that is designed to access an existing database. Known as the Load Definitions facility, it is located in the Tables tab of the Project Editor's Resource Browser.\">Load Definitions Facility</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofh1665702943152__li_d24581e1_d24582e1_d24583e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cck1665702542032.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cck1665702542032.html\" title=\"The /genSql switch generates DBMS-specific SQL command scripts for preparing an application database or the Uniface Repository, including creating tables and enforcing referential integrity constraints in the database.\">/genSql</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofh1665702943152__li_d24584e1_d24585e1_d24586e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xzp1665702623223.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xzp1665702623223.html\" title=\"SQL scripts for referential integrity can be generated with the IDE command line switch /genSql. The generated scripts map relationships defined in the application model to declarative constraints and database triggers in the database.\">Enable Referential Integrity in a Microsoft SQL Server Database</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530564\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530564\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Supported Utilities on Microsoft SQL Server Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Supported Utilities on Microsoft SQL Server The MSS connector supports the Create Table, Create Script, and Load Definitions facilities. For more information, see: Create Table Facility Create Script Facility Load Definitions Facility /genSql Enable Referential Integrity in a Microsoft SQL Server Database Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}